favorites.content: Don't cry because it's over. Smile because it happened.
favorites.author: Dr. Seuss

history.content: Experience is simply the name we give our mistakes.
history.author: Oscar Wilde

history.content: Do not waste yourself in rejection, nor bark against the bad, but chant the beauty of the good.
history.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

history.content: He that respects himself is safe from others; he wears a coat of mail that none can pierce.
history.author: Henry Wadsworth Longfellow

history.content: Happiness is when what you think, what you say, and what you do are in harmony.
history.author: Mahatma Gandhi

history.content: You cannot be lonely if you like the person you're alone with.
history.author: Wayne Dyer

history.content: The essence of true friendship is to make allowance for another's little lapses.
history.author: Ovid

quotes.content: Stay positive and happy. Work hard and don't give up hope.
quotes.author: Anonymous

quotes.content: Every day may not be good, but there is something good in every day.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
quotes.author: Steve Jobs
